  "text": "## Security Audit: HTTP Handlers Without Authentication Middleware\n\n### MIMIR Repository\n\nThe Mimir repository contains significant HTTP handler registrations without authentication middleware. Analysis of `/pkg/api/api.go` reveals the primary vulnerability pattern:\n\nThe `RegisterRoute()` function signature is: `func (a *API) RegisterRoute(path string, handler http.Handler, auth bool, gzipEnabled bool, ...)` where the third parameter `auth=false` indicates NO authentication middleware is applied.\n\n#### Unauthenticated HTTP Handlers in pkg/api/api.go (47 total):\n\n**Status and Debugging Endpoints (auth=false):**\n- Line 199: `/multitenant_alertmanager/status` - Alertmanager status\n- Line 200: `/multitenant_alertmanager/configs` - All alertmanager configs\n- Line 201: `/multitenant_alertmanager/ring` - Ring status\n- Line 203: `/alertmanager/api/v1/status/buildinfo` - Build information\n- Line 243: `/config` - Configuration handler\n- Line 244: `/` - Index page\n- Line 245: `/static/*` - Static files (prefix)\n- Line 246: `/debug/fgprof` - CPU profiler\n- Line 247: `/api/v1/status/buildinfo` - Build info\n- Line 248: `/api/v1/status/config` - Status config\n- Line 249: `/api/v1/status/flags` - Status flags\n- Line 259: `/runtime_config` - Runtime configuration\n- Line 363: `/prometheus/api/v1/status/buildinfo` - Prometheus build info\n- Line 469: `/prometheus/api/v1/status/buildinfo` - Prometheus build info (duplicate path)\n\n**Distributor Ring and Statistics (auth=false):**\n- Line 300: `/distributor/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n- Line 301: `/distributor/all_user_stats` - User statistics\n- Line 302: `/distributor/ha_tracker` - High availability tracker\n\n**Ingester Administrative Handlers (auth=false):**\n- Line 319: `/ingester/flush` - Flush ingester (GET, POST)\n- Line 320: `/ingester/prepare-shutdown` - Prepare shutdown (GET, POST, DELETE)\n- Line 321: `/ingester/prepare-partition-downscale` - Partition downscale (GET, POST, DELETE)\n- Line 322: `/ingester/prepare-instance-ring-downscale` - Instance ring downscale (GET, POST, DELETE)\n- Line 323: `/ingester/unregister-on-shutdown` - Unregister handler (GET, PUT, DELETE) **[NO GZIP]**\n- Line 324: `/ingester/shutdown` - Shutdown handler (POST)\n- Line 331: `/ingester/tenants` - List tenants\n- Line 332: `/ingester/tsdb/{tenant}` - Tenant TSDB info\n- Line 381: `/ingester/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n- Line 389: `/ingester/partition-ring` - Partition ring (GET, POST)\n\n**Ruler Administrative Handlers (auth=false):**\n- Line 341: `/ruler/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n- Line 347: `/ruler/rule_groups` - List all rule groups\n- Line 350: `/ruler/tenants` - List all tenants\n- Line 351: `/ruler/tenant/{tenant}/rule_groups` - Tenant rule groups\n\n**Store-Gateway Handlers (auth=false):**\n- Line 400: `/store-gateway/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n- Line 401: `/store-gateway/tenants` - List tenants\n- Line 402: `/store-gateway/tenant/{tenant}/blocks` - Tenant blocks\n- Line 403: `/store-gateway/prepare-shutdown` - Prepare shutdown (GET, POST, DELETE)\n\n**Compactor Handlers (auth=false):**\n- Line 412: `/compactor/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n- Line 419: `/compactor/tenants` - List tenants\n- Line 420: `/compactor/tenant/{tenant}/planned_jobs` - Planned jobs\n\n**Query Scheduler (auth=false):**\n- Line 450: `/querier/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n- Line 497: `/query-scheduler/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n\n**Overrides and Usage Tracking (auth=false):**\n- Line 307: Custom cost attribution registry path - Prometheus metrics **[NO GZIP]**\n- Line 507: `/overrides-exporter/ring` - Ring status (GET, POST)\n- Line 512: `/usage-tracker/prepare-instance-ring-downscale` - Ring downscale (GET, POST, DELETE)\n- Line 520: `/usage-tracker/instance-ring` - Instance ring (GET, POST)\n- Line 528: `/usage-tracker/partition-ring` - Partition ring (GET, POST)\n\n**Infrastructure Status (auth=false):**\n- Line 538: `/services` - Services status\n- Line 545: `/memberlist` - Memberlist status\n\n#### Direct HTTP Handler Registration in pkg/alertmanager/alertmanager.go:\n\nLines 338-341 register Grafana Alertmanager compatibility handlers directly on the internal mux without going through the central API authentication framework:\n```go\nam.mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/grafana/full_state\", http.HandlerFunc(am.GetFullStateHandler))\nam.mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/grafana/receivers\", http.HandlerFunc(am.GetReceiversHandler))\nam.mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/grafana/templates/test\", http.HandlerFunc(am.TestTemplatesHandler))\nam.mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/grafana/receivers/test\", http.HandlerFunc(am.TestReceiversHandler))\n```\n\nThese four handlers are registered via NewMultitenantAlertmanager() and bypass the API framework's centralized authentication middleware.\n\n### LOKI Repository\n\nThe Loki repository was not analyzed as the cloned repository contained only vendor dependencies with no source code.\n\n### Summary of Findings\n\n**Total Unprotected Endpoints: 51**\n- Mimir pkg/api/api.go: 47 routes with auth=false\n- Mimir pkg/alertmanager/alertmanager.go: 4 handlers without central auth\n\n**Key Risk Categories:**\n1. **Administrative Operations** - Shutdown, partition downscale, ring downscale operations are unauthenticated\n2. **Information Disclosure** - Tenant lists, block information, rule groups, and configuration are readable without auth\n3. **Operational Status** - Ring status, memberlist, services status exposed without authentication\n4. **Profiling and Debug** - `/debug/fgprof` CPU profiler is unauthenticated\n5. **Metrics** - Cost attribution metrics endpoint lacks gzip but also lacks authentication\n\n**Root Cause:** The API framework's RegisterRoute() function allows registering handlers with auth=false by design. These endpoints are likely intended to be operational/internal, but lack proper authentication guards, making sensitive operational information and administrative functions accessible without credentials."
